          </date>
        </CI_Citation>
      </citation>

      <abstract>
        <gco:CharacterString>
          County- and map-unit-level visualization of two USDA NRCS soil health
          interpretations derived from the National Cooperative Soil Survey (NCSS)
          SSURGO database: (1) Fragile Soil Index (FSI) — a composite measure of
          soil structural sensitivity to disturbance; and (2) SOH - Organic Matter
          Depletion — vulnerability of soil organic matter to tillage and management.

          Aggregation methodology: Dominant Condition. For each SSURGO map unit,
          the dominant interpretation class is the rating with the highest sum of
          major-component percentages (majcompflag = 'Yes', ordered by comppct_r DESC).
          County averages are area-weighted spatial intersections of map unit polygons
          against US Census TIGER county boundaries.

          Data are retrieved from the USDA SDA (Soil Data Access) REST API and
          refreshed on a quarterly basis following SSURGO update cycles.
        </gco:CharacterString>
      </abstract>

